data.text:
Viewers of Grey’s Anatomy Season 20 are wondering how many episodes are in the series and when each new episode comes out. It is an American medical drama that explores the personal and professional residents, attending & lives of intern physicians at the fictional Seattle Grace Hospital, later renamed Grey Sloan Memorial Hospital. The show focuses on the complexities of medical cases and the relationships between staff members. The doctors’ personal and professional struggles, triumphs, and growth are showcased as they progress from interns to experienced professionals.

Here’s how many episodes are in Grey’s Anatomy Season 20 and on what day new episodes come out.

How many episodes are in Grey’s Anatomy Season 20?

Grey’s Anatomy Season 20 is listed to have 10 episodes.

The list of the available episode information is as follows:

Episode 1: We’ve Only Just Begun

Episode 2: Keep the Family Close

Episode 3: Walk on the Ocean

In Season 20, the story continues after Meredith leaves to focus on Alzheimer’s research in Boston. The season unfolds amidst industry strikes, bringing fresh drama and medical challenges to Grey Sloan Memorial and the arrival of new interns. Meredith’s old house becomes the living quarters for three of the five recruits while the other two are secretly hooking up. The season has fewer episodes than its previous seasons.

The cast of this iconic medical series includes Chandra Wilson (Miranda Bailey), James Pickens Jr. (Richard Webber), Kevin McKidd (Owen Hunt), Caterina Scorsone (Amelia Shepherd), and Camilla Luddington (Jo Wilson) across all 10 episodes, navigating new medical and their personal dramas.

When do new Grey’s Anatomy Season 20 episodes come out?

New episodes of this critically acclaimed series created by Shonda Rhimes typically come out every Thursday.

The official synopsis for the series reads:

“Follows the personal and professional lives of a group of doctors at Seattle’s Grey Sloan Memorial Hospital.”
